rComments: A great TA. She goes above and beyond to make sure her students understand the material given in the lecture. Very approachable and so nice. Can sometimes be a hard grader on essays/papers, but it is always constructive criticism.

I thought Kasey was pretty good.  Granted, all she had to work with was what Professor Hoffman gave her, so you've got to let her slide a little bit.  But looking past all that, she's still really really hot.

Very helpful and understanding.  Section didn't cover lecture material, but articles that weren't really essential to the exams.  Nonetheless, interesting discussion.  She can be a hard grader on essays.
